result.name: 海景餐廳-V King Lounge/V King Restaurant

reviews.text: Great place right next to seaside with variety of alcohol choices. Strongly suggested

Great bar in Hung Hom!! If you want a bar for good old fashioned drinking with a great view, V King Lounge is the place for you!  Even though I moved to Yuen Long after 12 years living in Hung Hom, I still go back to V King Lounge at the weekends!

You can sit all by yourself in a ridiculously retro room with a full open view of HK Island drinking a very cold Hoegaarden. Food isn't something I'd go back for. Staff possibly not used to non-locals. 
Glimpse of the old Hong Kong that is going the way of the dodo.
France Marseille sea view
Great harbour view. Happy hour before 9pm.

reviews.text: Cheapest and fastest way to cross the harbour

It provides a quick and simple option to cross the harbour by ferry and get to North Point in around 10 minutes. It may be easier to take the ferry to North Point first then change to MTR, bus or taxi, than crossing the harbour through the tunnel and get stuck in traffic, especially as the MTR station at North Point is quite close to the ferry pier.

Ferry service from Hung Hom to North Point, not a very busy pier, the ferry service was not frequent, the price was just a bit cheaper than buses, but it can avoid the traffic jam in the Hong Kong Island and the cross harbour tunnel. It would be an alternative choice for travelling between Hung Hom and North Point, but need to pay attention to the business hour of the ferry service.

A bare bones ferry pier for ferries operating between 7am to 7pm plus. Its rather old, lacking in modern touches. Basic amenities, and some drinks vending machine in place. Next to the ferry terminal is a bus interchange. There's a restaurant attached to this building.
